ABC News anchor Peter Jennings has been diagnosed with lung cancer, prompting concern over the generational shift in network news anchors.
Despite his illness, Jennings plans to continue anchoring "World News Tonight" during treatment.
Colleagues express support as Jennings undergoes outpatient chemotherapy.
The absence of the iconic anchor poses a challenge for ABC, with potential substitutes like Charles Gibson and Elizabeth Vargas.
Viewers value the bond with familiar faces like Jennings, highlighting the evolving landscape of evening news.
As Jennings battles cancer, the future of network news remains uncertain, emphasizing the impact of his absence on ABC's competitive ratings race.
